  {
    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "The lint rule doesn't run on internal library code, but it does look at the _exported_ library types, since it can be used to help detect invalid library usage. These connector types get exported in the public API so they end up affecting the lint errors.\r\n\r\n\r\n> If it makes sense to enforce a specific style, we should enable [https://github.com/typescript-eslint/typescript-eslint/blob/main/packages/eslint-plugin/docs/rules/method-signature-style.md](https://github.com/typescript-eslint/typescript-eslint/blob/main/packages/eslint-plugin/docs/rules/method-signature-style.md?rgh-link-date=2022-05-30T08%3A52%3A35Z)\r\n\r\nThat's a good idea. One downside is that it looks like the InstantSearch.js library _does_ rely on `this` in certain places, so there are some function types where the non-arrow function might be more accurate. It doesn't change the runtime behavior though, so it's probably not a big deal.",
